862
01:02:53,812 --> 01:02:54,972
(WHISPERING) Just to help it.

863
01:02:58,692 --> 01:03:00,151
COFFEY: Don't be afraid.

864
01:03:00,652 --> 01:03:01,735
Help!

865
01:03:02,529 --> 01:03:05,281
Help! John Coffey's
killing Boss Edgecomb!

866
01:03:05,532 --> 01:03:07,116
Help!

867
01:03:07,200 --> 01:03:08,784
What are you doing?

868
01:03:08,910 --> 01:03:10,494
DEL: Help!

869
01:03:13,039 --> 01:03:14,707
Boss Howell! Help!

870
01:03:15,625 --> 01:03:17,376
(GRUNTS) Boss Stanton!
Somebody, come!

871
01:03:17,711 --> 01:03:19,712
Help!

872
01:03:21,423 --> 01:03:22,965
(PAUL GRUNTING)

873
01:03:27,637 --> 01:03:28,888
(SCREAMS)

874
01:03:32,726 --> 01:03:35,769
DEL: Help!

875
01:03:35,854 --> 01:03:38,189
Help! Boss Howell!
Boss Stanton!

876
01:03:38,565 --> 01:03:41,484
Somebody, come! John Coffey's
killing Boss Edgecomb!

877
01:03:41,568 --> 01:03:43,903
Del, for Christ sakes, shut up!

878
01:03:44,738 --> 01:03:45,863
(COFFEY COUGHING)

879
01:04:30,784 --> 01:04:32,868
What did you just do to me?

880
01:04:34,996 --> 01:04:36,580
I helped it.

881
01:04:37,749 --> 01:04:39,375
Didn't I help it?

882
01:04:40,460 --> 01:04:42,253
I just took it back, is all.

883
01:04:43,588 --> 01:04:45,464
Awful tired now, boss.

884
01:04:46,591 --> 01:04:47,925
Dog-tired.

885
01:05:12,450 --> 01:05:15,202
DEL: Boss,
what that man do to you?

886
01:05:38,560 --> 01:05:40,269
(UNZIPPING)

887
01:05:42,147 --> 01:05:44,523
(URINATING)

888
01:05:55,368 --> 01:05:56,869
(SIGHS)

889
01:06:01,207 --> 01:06:03,083
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

890
01:06:04,169 --> 01:06:06,378
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

891
01:06:17,891 --> 01:06:20,351
Hey, honey.
How you feeling?

892
01:06:22,479 --> 01:06:24,688
Oh, not too bad.

893
01:06:26,399 --> 01:06:27,524
What did the doctor say?

894
01:06:30,528 --> 01:06:32,321
Oh, you know doctors.

895
01:06:32,739 --> 01:06:34,573
Gobbledygook, mostly.

896
01:06:35,617 --> 01:06:37,076
Gobbledygook.

897
01:06:49,089 --> 01:06:50,589
(CLICKS TONGUE)

898
01:06:52,258 --> 01:06:53,884
Having stew tonight.

899
01:07:04,104 --> 01:07:05,854
What are you doing?

900
01:07:12,737 --> 01:07:14,613
What does it feel like?

901
01:07:15,281 --> 01:07:17,616
Well, I know what it feels like.

902
01:07:21,579 --> 01:07:23,455
It feels great.

903
01:07:32,674 --> 01:07:35,300
(JAN MOANING) (BED CREAKING)

904
01:07:42,726 --> 01:07:45,144
(PAUL MOANING)

905
01:07:50,150 --> 01:07:51,400
JAN: Mmm.

906
01:07:57,741 --> 01:07:59,491
Paul.
Yeah?

907
01:08:00,076 --> 01:08:01,910
Not that I'm complaining...

908
01:08:01,995 --> 01:08:03,287
Uh-huh.

909
01:08:03,997 --> 01:08:07,541
But we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 19.

910
01:08:07,625 --> 01:08:09,418
Yeah, we did,
at your mom's, yeah.

911
01:08:09,502 --> 01:08:10,794
Mmm-hmm.

912
01:08:11,796 --> 01:08:14,006
Wanna tell me what's going on?

913
01:08:14,090 --> 01:08:15,340
(PANTING)

914
01:08:17,427 --> 01:08:18,844
Well...

915
01:08:20,346 --> 01:08:22,097
See, the thing is...

916
01:08:23,641 --> 01:08:26,727
I never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

917
01:08:30,190 --> 01:08:32,649
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

918
01:08:33,151 --> 01:08:35,569
I'm thinking of taking
the morning off sick.

919
01:08:35,653 --> 01:08:37,696
You cover the fort for me?

920
01:08:38,698 --> 01:08:40,991
That's swell. Thanks.

921
01:08:41,075 --> 01:08:43,952
Yeah, no. (STAMMERING)
I'm sure I'll feel better.

922
01:08:44,037 --> 01:08:45,913
Okay. Okay.

923
01:08:52,045 --> 01:08:53,325
You're sure
you ought to do this?

924
01:08:55,632 --> 01:08:57,549
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

925
01:09:14,692 --> 01:09:17,110
Burt, you got some company.

926
01:09:18,363 --> 01:09:20,113
Can I offer you a cold drink?

927
01:09:20,198 --> 01:09:22,866
Oh, yes, ma'am. A cold drink
would be fine. Thank you.

928
01:09:23,618 --> 01:09:24,898
Mr. Hammersmith,
your office said

929
01:09:24,953 --> 01:09:26,829
I might find you at home today.

930
01:09:26,913 --> 01:09:28,580
Hope I'm not troubling you.

931
01:09:29,249 --> 01:09:31,416
Well, that depends, Mr...

932
01:09:31,501 --> 01:09:35,587
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block
supervisor up on Cold Mountain.

933
01:09:36,840 --> 01:09:38,340
The Green Mile.

934
01:09:38,424 --> 01:09:41,385
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

935
01:09:42,262 --> 01:09:43,971
I'd like to ask you
about one of 'em.

936
01:09:44,055 --> 01:09:46,098
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

937
01:09:46,182 --> 01:09:48,141
Have a seat.
Thank you.

938
01:09:52,814 --> 01:09:53,939
Which client?

939
01:09:54,023 --> 01:09:55,274
(CLEARS THROAT)

940
01:09:56,150 --> 01:09:58,569
Now you got my
curiosity aroused.

941
01:09:59,153 --> 01:10:00,487
John Coffey.

942
01:10:00,572 --> 01:10:01,572
Ah.

943
01:10:01,656 --> 01:10:03,198
Coffey.

944
01:10:03,283 --> 01:10:04,575
He causing you problems?

945
01:10:04,951 --> 01:10:06,535
No. No, can't say he is.

946
01:10:06,619 --> 01:10:08,745
He doesn't like the dark
and cries on occasion,

947
01:10:08,830 --> 01:10:10,539
but other than that...

948
01:10:10,623 --> 01:10:13,917
He cries, does he? Well, got
a lot to cry about, I'd say.

949
01:10:14,252 --> 01:10:15,794
You know what he did.

950
01:10:16,504 --> 01:10:18,297
I read the court transcript.

951
01:10:19,507 --> 01:10:20,507
Thank you, missus.

952
01:10:20,592 --> 01:10:21,800
My pleasure.

953
01:10:23,219 --> 01:10:26,221
Kids! Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

954
01:10:26,556 --> 01:10:27,931
BOTH: Coming, Mama!

955
01:10:28,016 --> 01:10:31,101
What exactly are you
trying to find out?

956
01:10:31,811 --> 01:10:34,146
I've wondered if he ever did
anything like that before.

957
01:10:35,607 --> 01:10:37,566
Why? Has he said anything?

958
01:10:37,650 --> 01:10:40,360
No, but a man who
does a thing like that

959
01:10:41,154 --> 01:10:43,238
has often developed
a taste for it over time.

960
01:10:43,323 --> 01:10:45,115
It occurred to me

961
01:10:45,199 --> 01:10:47,784
that it might be easy enough
to follow his back trail.

962
01:10:47,869 --> 01:10:49,161
Find out.

963
01:10:49,829 --> 01:10:53,332
A man his size, and colored to
boot, can't be that hard to trace.

964
01:10:53,875 --> 01:10:57,127
You'd think so,
but you'd be wrong.

965
01:10:57,211 --> 01:10:59,379
Believe me, we tried.

966
01:11:00,089 --> 01:11:01,548
Like he'd dropped
out of the sky.

967
01:11:03,092 --> 01:11:04,676
How can that be?

968
01:11:04,761 --> 01:11:06,595
We're in a depression.

969
01:11:06,679 --> 01:11:08,931
A third of the country's
out of work.

970
01:11:09,015 --> 01:11:10,933
People are drifting
by the thousands,

971
01:11:11,017 --> 01:11:13,268
looking for jobs,
for greener grass.

972
01:11:13,353 --> 01:11:16,438
Even a giant like Coffey wouldn't
get noticed everywhere he goes.

973
01:11:17,315 --> 01:11:19,608
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

974
01:11:20,485 --> 01:11:21,860
He is, uh...

975
01:11:22,445 --> 01:11:24,488
strange, I admit.

976
01:11:24,864 --> 01:11:28,659
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

977
01:11:29,619 --> 01:11:32,079
I know violent men,
Mr. Hammersmith.

978
01:11:32,163 --> 01:11:34,206
I deal with them
day in and day out.

979
01:11:35,917 --> 01:11:37,197
You didn't come
up here to ask me

980
01:11:37,210 --> 01:11:38,669
whether he might
have killed before.

981
01:11:38,753 --> 01:11:41,046
You came up here to see
if I think he did it at all.

982
01:11:43,091 --> 01:11:44,716
Do you?
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

983
01:11:46,052 --> 01:11:48,303
One seldom sees
a less ambiguous case.

984
01:11:48,388 --> 01:11:50,514
He was found with
the victims in his arms.

985
01:11:50,598 --> 01:11:52,265
And yet you defended him.

986
01:11:53,393 --> 01:11:55,477
Everyone is entitled
to a defense.

987
01:11:56,521 --> 01:11:58,313
CYNTHIA: Kids! Lunch!

988
01:11:58,398 --> 01:11:59,690
Y'all listen to your mama now!

989
01:12:04,237 --> 01:12:06,196
I'll tell you something.

990
01:12:06,906 --> 01:12:09,106
And you listen close, too,
because it might be something

991
01:12:09,158 --> 01:12:10,659
you need to know.

992
01:12:10,743 --> 01:12:12,077
I'm listening.

993
01:12:13,454 --> 01:12:14,579
We had us a dog.

994
01:12:15,623 --> 01:12:17,708
Just a sweet mongrel.

995
01:12:17,792 --> 01:12:19,292
You know the kind.

996
01:12:20,753 --> 01:12:24,089
Well, in many ways, a good
mongrel dog is like a Negro.

997
01:12:24,966 --> 01:12:26,717
You get to know it.

998
01:12:27,051 --> 01:12:31,471
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use,

999
01:12:31,556 --> 01:12:34,516
but you keep it around because
you think it loves you.

1000
01:12:34,600 --> 01:12:36,226
(CHUCKLES)

1001
01:12:36,602 --> 01:12:38,186
if you're lucky,
Mr. Edgecomb,

1002
01:12:38,271 --> 01:12:40,814
you never have to
find out any different.

1003
01:12:41,774 --> 01:12:43,191
My wife and I were not so lucky.

1004
01:12:45,945 --> 01:12:47,487
Caleb, come here for a second.

1005
01:12:48,823 --> 01:12:50,157
Come here.

1006
01:12:51,492 --> 01:12:52,743
Please, Son.

1007
01:12:54,328 --> 01:12:56,246
He still has the one good eye.

1008
01:12:58,166 --> 01:13:00,542
I suppose he's lucky

1009
01:13:00,626 --> 01:13:02,711
not to be completely blind.

1010
01:13:05,673 --> 01:13:09,176
We get down on our knees and thank
God for that much at least.

1011
01:13:10,136 --> 01:13:11,595
Right, Caleb?

1012
01:13:13,973 --> 01:13:15,390
Okay, go on in now.

1013
01:13:16,142 --> 01:13:17,601
(DOOR OPENING)

1014
01:13:17,685 --> 01:13:18,769
(DOOR CLOSING)

1015
01:13:18,853 --> 01:13:21,563
That dog attacked
my boy for no reason.

1016
01:13:22,356 --> 01:13:24,357
Just got it in his mind one day.

1017
01:13:25,318 --> 01:13:26,902
The same with John Coffey.

1018
01:13:26,986 --> 01:13:31,156
He was sorry afterwards.
Of that I have no doubt.

1019
01:13:31,908 --> 01:13:33,909
But those little girls...

1020
01:13:33,993 --> 01:13:36,161
stayed raped and murdered.

1021
01:13:37,080 --> 01:13:39,081
Maybe he'd never done it before.

1022
01:13:40,833 --> 01:13:42,834
My dog never bit before.

1023
01:13:44,754 --> 01:13:47,380
But I didn't concern
myself with that.

1024
01:13:48,508 --> 01:13:49,883
I went out there with my rifle

1025
01:13:49,967 --> 01:13:52,511
and grabbed his collar
and blew his brains out.

1026
01:13:53,846 --> 01:13:54,971
Is Coffey guilty?

1027
01:13:57,975 --> 01:13:59,684
Yes, he is.

1028
01:14:00,186 --> 01:14:01,186
Don't you doubt it.

1029
01:14:02,313 --> 01:14:04,856
And don't you turn
your back on him.

1030
01:14:05,650 --> 01:14:07,025
You may get away with it once

1031
01:14:07,527 --> 01:14:09,528
or even a hundred times.

1032
01:14:10,655 --> 01:14:12,197
But in the end,

1033
01:14:14,325 --> 01:14:15,867
you'll get bit.

1034
01:14:17,203 --> 01:14:19,329
(MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY)
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1035
01:14:28,381 --> 01:14:30,882
Oh, me! Oh, my!

1036
01:14:33,094 --> 01:14:34,845
PAUL: John.

1037
01:14:34,929 --> 01:14:36,221
John.

1038
01:14:37,723 --> 01:14:39,850
I'm smelling me some corn bread.

1039
01:14:40,393 --> 01:14:42,185
It's from my missus.

1040
01:14:45,982 --> 01:14:48,316
She wanted to thank you.

1041
01:14:49,735 --> 01:14:51,111
Thank me for what?

1042
01:14:51,571 --> 01:14:53,071
Well, you know.

1043
01:14:55,575 --> 01:14:56,950
(WHISPERS) For helping me.

1044
