Go on, you can do it.

2318
02:55:41,781 --> 02:55:45,659
This isn't exactly the Mouseville
we had in mind, is it?

2319
02:55:47,120 --> 02:55:50,414
But we make do.
Don't we, old fella?

2320
02:55:57,505 --> 02:56:00,424
I think Mr. Jingles
happened by accident.

2321
02:56:01,676 --> 02:56:06,055
I think when we electrocuted
Del, and it all went so badly...

2322
02:56:06,640 --> 02:56:08,891
Well, John could
feel that, you know.

2323
02:56:09,392 --> 02:56:11,977
And I think a part of

2324
02:56:13,063 --> 02:56:15,731
whatever magic was inside of him

2325
02:56:15,815 --> 02:56:18,484
just leapt into
my tiny friend here.

2326
02:56:20,362 --> 02:56:21,987
As for me,

2327
02:56:23,448 --> 02:56:25,908
John had to give me
a part of himself,

2328
02:56:26,451 --> 02:56:28,744
a gift, the way he saw it,

2329
02:56:28,828 --> 02:56:31,789
so that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

2330
02:56:34,668 --> 02:56:36,418
When John did that,

2331
02:56:38,463 --> 02:56:40,256
when he took my hand,

2332
02:56:41,758 --> 02:56:43,509
a part of the power

2333
02:56:44,094 --> 02:56:45,678
that worked through him

2334
02:56:46,513 --> 02:56:48,097
spilled into me.

2335
02:56:48,932 --> 02:56:50,182
He what?

2336
02:56:51,017 --> 02:56:54,645
He infected you with life?

2337
02:56:56,189 --> 02:56:58,274
It's as good a word as any.

2338
02:56:59,985 --> 02:57:04,029
He infected us both, didn't he, Mr.
Jingles? With life.

2339
02:57:08,702 --> 02:57:11,036
I'm 108 years old, Elaine.

2340
02:57:11,997 --> 02:57:15,541
I was 44 the year that John
Coffey walked the Green Mile.

2341
02:57:19,212 --> 02:57:21,130
You mustn't blame John.

2342
02:57:21,673 --> 02:57:23,132
He couldn't help what happened.

2343
02:57:23,216 --> 02:57:26,510
He was...
He's just a force of nature.

2344
02:57:28,096 --> 02:57:31,890
Oh, I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

2345
02:57:33,518 --> 02:57:35,728
Another century come to pass.

2346
02:57:36,730 --> 02:57:38,063
But I've...

2347
02:57:39,274 --> 02:57:43,444
I've had to see my friends and loved
ones die off through the years.

2348
02:57:44,195 --> 02:57:45,779
Hal and Melinda,

2349
02:57:46,614 --> 02:57:48,115
Brutus Howell,

2350
02:57:48,199 --> 02:57:50,409
my wife, my boy.

2351
02:57:53,872 --> 02:57:55,456
And you, Elaine.

2352
02:57:56,791 --> 02:57:58,417
You'll die, too.

2353
02:57:59,961 --> 02:58:03,672
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

2354
02:58:05,884 --> 02:58:07,968
It's my atonement, you see.

2355
02:58:08,887 --> 02:58:10,554
It's my punishment

2356
02:58:10,847 --> 02:58:13,432
for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning,

2357
02:58:15,226 --> 02:58:17,436
for killing a miracle of God.

2358
02:58:19,356 --> 02:58:21,774
PRIEST: Almighty,
everlasting God,

2359
02:58:22,650 --> 02:58:24,610
the source of all
being and life...

2360
02:58:25,362 --> 02:58:29,114
PAUL: You'll be gone like all the others.
I'll have to stay.

2361
02:58:31,534 --> 02:58:34,995
Oh, I'll die eventually.
Of that I'm sure.

2362
02:58:36,331 --> 02:58:39,458
I have no illusions
of immortality.

2363
02:58:40,627 --> 02:58:42,961
But I will have wished for death

2364
02:58:43,630 --> 02:58:45,714
long before death finds me.

2365
02:58:47,384 --> 02:58:50,344
In truth, I wish for it already.

2366
02:58:50,428 --> 02:58:52,638
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

2367
02:58:56,976 --> 02:58:58,602
(SOFT SQUEAKING)

2368
02:59:03,233 --> 02:59:04,650
Mr. Jingles?

2369
02:59:14,160 --> 02:59:15,953
Where you been, hmm?

2370
02:59:16,704 --> 02:59:20,833
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry, hmm?

2371
02:59:20,917 --> 02:59:23,252
Let's go see if we can't
find you something to eat.

2372
02:59:24,504 --> 02:59:26,255
A few crumbs anyway.

2373
02:59:26,339 --> 02:59:28,257
I know you'd like that.

2374
02:59:29,551 --> 02:59:31,552
Look at you. Mr. Jingles.

2375
02:59:32,637 --> 02:59:35,848
I lie in bed most nights
thinking about it.

2376
02:59:36,683 --> 02:59:38,058
And I wait.

2377
02:59:39,352 --> 02:59:42,438
I think about all
the people I've loved,

2378
02:59:42,522 --> 02:59:44,022
now long gone.

2379
02:59:45,483 --> 02:59:47,985
I think about my beautiful Jan,

2380
02:59:48,069 --> 02:59:50,487
how I lost her
so many years ago.

2381
02:59:52,365 --> 02:59:57,411
And I think about all of us
walking our own Green Mile,

2382
02:59:57,495 --> 02:59:59,288
each in our own time.

2383
03:00:01,082 --> 03:00:04,209
But one thought
more than any other

2384
03:00:04,294 --> 03:00:06,378
keeps me awake most nights.

2385
03:00:08,173 --> 03:00:11,425
If he could make
a mouse live so long,

2386
03:00:12,677 --> 03:00:14,720
how much longer do I have?

2387
03:00:19,142 --> 03:00:21,560
We each owe a death.

2388
03:00:22,145 --> 03:00:24,104
There are no exceptions.

2389
03:00:25,356 --> 03:00:26,815
But, oh, God,

2390
03:00:28,401 --> 03:00:30,068
sometimes,

2391
03:00:30,695 --> 03:00:33,530
the Green Mile seems so long.

